"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The hue parameter in sns.scatterplot is expected to be either categorical or numeric. However, when it is numeric, color mapping will behave differently. In this case, 'color' is of type int64 which is numeric, but the color palette is set as if 'color' is categorical. This might lead to unexpected color mapping behavior.\", \"patch\": \"11,12c11\\n< colors = ['#747FE3', '#8EE35D', '#E37346']\\n< sns.set_palette(sns.color_palette(colors))\\n---\\n> sns.set_palette('viridis')\\n\"}"